Research tab (Phase 1 focus: IDA)
Research is where we connect real researcher tooling to LLM workflows. The Research section contains multiple tool tabs, but Phase 1 intentionally focuses on IDA as the first complete experience. JADX and Ghidra appear as “Coming soon” to show direction without implying full support.

The IDA page tells a simple truth: the IDA MCP server must run next to IDA on the researcher’s own workstation. The portal does not try to host IDA centrally. Instead, the portal makes the connection repeatable, supportable, and governable.

The flow is described in the UI as a guided setup. We install the package via pip using a command we provide, run the package’s install/setup command, then configure the MCP address inside IDA. After the local side is ready, we return to the portal and register the workstation hostname and IDA port. Submitting this form updates the managed Nginx mapping layer (already implemented) and persists the registration to the DB so we can see status, ownership, and history.

Next to that setup area, the page also supports the collaboration model: it points to the Bitbucket repository that produces the pip package, encourages contributions of tools and improvements, and shows version/changelog information so researchers can choose which package version to install.

Finally, Phase 1 documents an optional next step: after registration, the portal can attempt to configure OpenWebUI/LibreChat so the MCP server appears inside the user’s chat environment — but only in a private way (visible only to that user or to a group that effectively contains only them). If the platform cannot guarantee per-user isolation, this step must remain optional and gated; the safe alternative is letting users configure the MCP server locally (e.g., in Cline) without publishing it to a shared central system.

Ownership is explicit: IDA registrations are stored in the DB; users can delete their own registration (which removes both DB record and Nginx mapping), and admins can delete any user’s registration.



